ne Ellis Jr. (26 May 1912 – 15 March 2000) was an American football and basketball coach. He was the head football coach at Jackson State University in Jackson, Mississippi. He led the Tigers to a 24–21–3 record from 1946 to 1951 before being replaced by future College Football Hall of Fame coach John Merritt. He was educated at Morehouse College and Boston University.', 'Will Muschamp | William Larry Muschamp (born August 3, 1971) is an American football coach and former player. He is currently the head coach at the University of South Carolina. He was previously the head coach at the University of Florida from 2011 to 2014.'], 'question': 'Which American football coach has both a TV and radio show named after him which are hosted by Todd Ellis?', 'reasoning': 'The question asks which American football coach has both a TV and radio show named after him which are hosted by Todd Ellis. The context provides information about Todd Ellis being the "Voice of the Gamecocks" and hosting TV and radio shows. The context also mentions Will Muschamp, who is the head coach at the University of South Carolina. Therefore, it can be inferred that Will Muschamp is the coach who has both a TV and radio show named after him which are hosted by Todd Ellis.', 'answer': 'Will Muschamp'}) (input_keys=None)]

